Hook and Mode together carry a cost multiplier that applies to the spell's total outer variable cost.
Simple physical interactions default to x1. Effects operating at the identity, soul, or fundamental-law level
carry multipliers from x10 to x100. This is how T7–T9 costs are reached: the outer variables describe what
the sigil is shaped to do; Hook and Mode describe how deeply the Flux must reach to do it.

| Level        | Multiplier |
|--------------|------------|
| Basic        | x1         |
| Moderate     | x2         |
| Significant  | x4         |
| Extreme      | x10        |
| Transcendent | x30        |
